---
source: tests/cli_golden.rs
expression: help
---
Enable a plugin in `AURA_HOME/config.toml` (`enabled = true`).

When the cached manifest has `trust.require_explicit_trust = true` and the plugin is not already trusted in operator config, the flow prompts the operator on the TTY. `--yes` skips the prompt and accepts trust; `--no` skips the prompt and declines (the plugin is NOT enabled).

Usage: aura plugins enable [OPTIONS] <ID>

Arguments:
  <ID>
          Plugin id (matches the manifest `id` field)

Options:
      --mode <MODE>
          Phase 9: top-level `AgentMode` override. Highest rung of the documented resolution priority chain (CLI > TUI slash > SDK field > daemon default > `AgentMode::Agent` fallback). The flag is resolved at session start by the fleet daemon's `resolve_session_mode` helper

          Possible values:
          - agent: Full unrestricted operation subject to user permissions
          - plan:  Read + markdown writes + read-only subprocesses
          - ask:   Read-only
          - debug: Read + sandboxed probes only

      --yes
          Bypass the trust prompt and accept trust automatically. Mutually exclusive with `--no`

      --no
          Bypass the trust prompt and decline trust automatically. Mutually exclusive with `--yes`

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
